# Obsidian frontmatter strip.
#
# This repository sits inside an Obsidian vault whose maintenance script
# (<vault>/.obsidian/add_properties.py, fired from a detached Claude Code PostToolUse
# hook) stamps `project:` / `type:` / `authorship:` / `tags:` frontmatter -- and
# sometimes a "## Related notes (Obsidian)" footer -- into these documents, and rewrites
# them as CRLF.  They are tracked, so without a filter that metadata lands in the public
# history and the tree is dirty after every edit.
#
# The `obsidian-strip` clean filter keeps the metadata in the WORKING TREE (Obsidian
# needs it) while git stores the clean, LF-normalized version.  It needs per-clone local
# config, which is NOT carried by `git clone`:
#
#     sh scripts/setup-clone.sh
#
# or, by hand:
#
#     git config filter.obsidian-strip.clean "python scripts/strip-obsidian-frontmatter.py"
#     git config filter.obsidian-strip.smudge cat
#
# Without that config git leaves the content untouched and the frontmatter would be
# committable -- so .githooks/pre-commit independently rejects any staged document that
# still carries a vault frontmatter block, and tells you to run setup-clone.sh.
#
# Keep this list in sync with what the stamper touches: its in_scope() matches a repo's
# CLAUDE.md, README.md, AGENTS.md, and anything under plans/ or docs/.
/CLAUDE.md    filter=obsidian-strip
/README.md    filter=obsidian-strip
/AGENTS.md    filter=obsidian-strip
/docs/*.md    filter=obsidian-strip
